-- Parcel Bomb Addressed to Sarkozy Is Among Two Defused by Police in Athens
-- B y   M a r i a   P e t r a k i s
-- 2010-11-01T13:49:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-01/parcel-bomb-addressed-to-sarkozy-is-among-two-defused-by-police-in-athens.html
Greek police defused two parcel bombs
found on two men arrested after a separate parcel bomb exploded
in an Athens suburb today, slightly injuring a woman.  The two bombs were addressed to the Belgian embassy and to
French President Nicolas Sarkozy, according to an e-mailed
statement from the Athens-based headquarters of the Greek
Police.  The two men, aged 22 and 24, were found in possession of
two handguns, wigs and a bulletproof vest, according to the
statement. The 22-year-old, who wasnâ€™t named, has an outstanding
warrant against him for involvement in a group called Conspiracy
of the Nuclei of Fire, according to the statement.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
